2	207	AKT1	AKT1, also referred to as protein kinase B, has been known as an oncogene for quite some time. AKT activation relies on the PI3K pathway, and is recognized as a critical node in the pathway. The E17 hotspot is the most characterized of AKT1 mutations, and has been shown to result in activation of the protein. Mutations in AKT1 have also been shown to confer resistance to allosteric kinase inhibitors in vitro.	v-akt murine thymoma viral oncogene homolog 1	2015-02-05 21:09:34.525528	2015-02-05 21:09:34.525528	\N
